# 2. 助っ人登場！

Tsukasa: Hmm...
Tsukasa: (We're back at the Wonder Stage following the conclusion of our ambassadorial performances...)
Tsukasa: (But we haven't been receiving the same sort of stimulation as before.)
Tsukasa: (Of course, I couldn't be happier to be back at the Wonder Stage making the audience smile. This is our home and there's plenty we can still do here.)
Tsukasa: (However...)
Tsukasa: (I want more of those opportunities... I want to keep growing as an actor.)
Tsukasa: (I could conceivably train with some other troupes to hone my craft... But...)
Tsukasa: (I'm the troupe leader of Wonderlands×Showtime. I can't just leave because I feel like it.)
Rui: You care deeply about doing your best as a cast member of Phoenix Wonderland and making your own dream come true...
Tsukasa: Both things, huh...?
Tsukasa: What?! It's already this late...?! I need to get to practice!
Nene: And so, Tsukasanosuke and his merry group of friends continued to make everybody all across the land smile. The end.
Rui: Okay, our final rehearsal went beautifully. We should be more than ready for tomorrow's performance...
Emu: Yeah! Let's make it a super happy New Year's for everyone♪
Tsukasa: Yes, let's! A happy performance to kick off the new year!
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP...
Tsukasa: Hm...?
Tsukasa: You've been awfully quiet today... Just yesterday you were running all over the place.
Robo-Nene: Shall I run a check?
Tsukasa: Whoa! You scared me! Also, check? Check what...?
Rui: In simple terms, she'll be running a diagnostic check on him to make sure he's functioning properly.
Emu: Does that mean she can figure out if Lion Dance Robot's sick...?!
Nene: Then, if you don't mind.
Robo-Nene: Understood. Commencing diagnostic check.
Robo-Nene: Check complete. No issues detected.
Tsukasa: Hm? Really?
Robo-Nene: Yes. However, if I were to put my finger on it...
Robo-Nene: He seems to be feeling a little down.
Emu: What?! Lion Dance Robot's feeling sad?! Why?! Our show's tomorrow!
Tsukasa: Wait, a robot can feel sad...?
Rui: It could be because our show is tomorrow.
Nene: Huh?
Rui: Lion Dance Robot seemed very happy when I brought him out of storage the other day since he usually only gets to come out and play around New Year's.
Rui: So, I suspect that he's feeling a bit down because he knows that he'll have to go away for a while after tomorrow's performance...
Emu: Then, let's make it so he gets to appear in shows all year round! Not just during New Year's!
Emu: I mean, it's so much fun to do all sorts of shows in all sorts of different places!
Rui: True... As much I'd like to do that...
Rui: I built Lion Dance Robot with a fairly specific purpose in mind. Unfortunately, his functions are limited, so it may be difficult to make him more versatile.
Emu: What?! But...
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP...
Tsukasa: ...
Tsukasa: (In other words, Lion Dance Robot would look very out of place if he were to perform in a show that's not about New Year's...)
Tsukasa: (He may be a robot, but it does seem like he wants to be in more shows...)
Tsukasa: (He may even stand to gain quite a lot if we were to somehow make that possible for him...)
Tsukasa: Then, why don't we try performing in a variety of different places outside of the Wonder Stage?
Emu: A wide variety of places?! That sounds fun!
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP CHOMP!
Nene: Y-You mean starting now? How are we gonna do that? It's New Year's Eve, and we need a way to transport Lion Dance Robot and Robo-Nene.
Rui: We'd also have to receive permission to perform wherever we go. That's going to take a bit of time...
Tsukasa: R-Right... Wait, I know! Emu, can't we ask your brothers for some help?!
Emu: Oh, right! They could help us get permission to perform!
Emu: No, hang on... They're gonna be busy attending all these New Year's parties and stuff, so they might not be able to help...
Tsukasa: Grr...! Then, we just have to find someone else who can...
???: Oh, are you all done rehearsing?
Tsukasa: Hm? That voice...
Emu: Hi, Sis!
Nene: Huh? Sis...? Emu, is she your big sister?
Rui: Yes, I do remember hearing that she has an older sister...
Hinata: Hehe. It's nice to meet you all. I'm Emu's big sister, Hinata.
Hinata: You must be Tsukasa, Nene and Rui. I've been meaning to meet all of you for quite some time now.
Tsukasa: L-Likewise! We are honored!
Emu: Anyway, Sis, what are you doing here? Did you need something?
Hinata: Oh, I was actually hoping to use your New Year's show as reference for something.
Tsukasa: Our show? As reference...?
Hinata: Yes, I'm studying how to make it so children can have more fun while learning.
Hinata: As it turns out, I'll be doing some field training at a preschool and putting on a little performance for the children there.
Hinata: So, since you're very popular with children, I was hoping to have them see your show.
Rui: I see. Thank you for explaining.
Hinata: Not a problem. But I seem to have missed my opportunity since you've already finished practicing...
Hinata: At the same time, I'm glad I came since I got to overhear a lovely conversation.
Tsukasa: Huh?
Hinata: You were just talking about doing shows in various different places, no? I'd like to help you with that, and I can drive if need be.
Emu: S-Sis...! Thank you! This is so wonderhoy!
Tsukasa: A-Are you sure?!
Hinata: Of course! Not only do I want to see your show, but I'd also love to help out.
Tsukasa: ...! Thank you very much! Then, we happily accept!
